    "product-slider": {
      "type": "product-slider",
      "blocks": {
        "slide-1": {
          "type": "slide",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/sheesham_wood_king_size_bed_with_hydraulic_storage.png",
            "heading": "Sheesham Hydraulic Storage Beds",
            "text": "<p>These designs prioritize storage volume over everything else. When you lift the mattress platform, you get access to nearly the entire footprint of the bed—nothing else in the collection offers this much dedicated storage space. This makes a sheesham wood king size bed with storage, especially in a hydraulic configuration, one of the most space-efficient choices for modern homes. The hydraulic mechanism does add weight (these beds run 200–220 lbs) and requires clearance behind the bed, but for people with limited closet space or who need to store luggage, off-season clothes, or extra bedding, the tradeoff makes sense.</p>",
            "button_label": "Shop Now",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/beds"
          }
        },
        "slide-2": {
          "type": "slide",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/sheesham_wood_king_size_bed_with_storage_drawers.png",
            "heading": "Drawer Storage Beds",
            "text": "<p>If you've ever wished your bed could function like a dresser, these designs deliver that. Separate drawers mean you can dedicate one to bedding, another to off-season clothes, another to items you want hidden but accessible.The drawer configurations vary—some designs feature two deep drawers on one side, others distribute four to six smaller drawers around the base. Choose based on what you're storing and which side of your bed has clearance space.</p>",
            "button_label": "Shop Now",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/beds"
          }
        },
        "slide-3": {
          "type": "slide",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/sheesham_wood_king_size_bed_with_box_storage.png",
            "heading": "Box Storage Beds",
            "text": "<p>These beds give you enclosed underbed storage without complex mechanisms. The space underneath is paneled on three sides with open access from the front or end—you decide how to organize it with your own bins, baskets, or storage solutions.This design works especially well if you already have a storage system you like, if you're storing irregular items that don't fit in drawers, or if you want solid wood bed construction without the premium hardware costs.</p>",
            "button_label": "Shop Now",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/beds"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "slide-1",
        "slide-2",
        "slide-3"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "background_color": "#ffffff"
      }
    },
    "info-columns": {
      "type": "info-columns",
      "blocks": {
        "column_YhFaU6": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 40,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "Density and weight capacity",
            "text": "<p>Sheesham's density (around 770 kg/m³) sits between oak and walnut. This means side rails, headboards, and slat systems resist denting and support weight without sagging over time. Storage beds need to handle more stress than standard beds since they're heavier and users frequently access storage mechanisms. Sheesham handles this reliably.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "column_hKBqGb": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 40,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "Humidity resistance",
            "text": "<p>The wood contains natural oils that help it withstand moisture exposure better than lighter woods like mango or rubber wood. This matters because storage beds create enclosed spaces underneath where air circulation is limited. In humid climates, woods without natural moisture resistance can warp or attract insects. Sheesham's oil content provides built-in protection.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "column_xmirW4": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 40,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "Movement stability",
            "text": "<p>Wood expands and contracts with seasonal humidity changes. Sheesham's interlocked grain structure limits this movement to about 3-5% seasonally, compared to 7-12% for many other furniture woods. In practical terms, your drawer runners won't suddenly stick during monsoon season and loosen in winter. The tolerances stay consistent year-round.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "col-1": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 100,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "Longevity",
            "text": "<p>The solid sheesham wood beds typically last 15-20 years with normal use before you see any structural issues. The wood itself can go 50+ years—the limiting factors are usually hardware wear (hydraulic pistons, drawer slides) rather than wood failure. If you're buying quality construction with proper joinery, this bed outlasts most other bedroom furniture investments.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "col-2": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 40,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "Visual character",
            "text": "<p>Sheesham has a distinctive wavy, interlocked grain pattern with natural color variation from golden browns to deep chocolate tones. This means no two beds look identical—even beds from the same design will have unique grain patterns. This variability is an authenticity marker, not a quality concern.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "col-3": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon_size": 40,
            "icon_gap": 14,
            "heading": "The tradeoff",
            "text": "<p>Sheesham beds are heavy. A king-size storage bed typically weighs 180-220 lbs, making assembly a two-person job and delivery logistics more complex. But this weight directly correlates with the structural integrity and lifespan you're getting.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "column_YhFaU6",
        "column_hKBqGb",
        "column_xmirW4",
        "col-1",
        "col-2",
        "col-3"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "section_heading": "Why Sheesham Wood Across Our Collection?",
        "columns_per_row": 3,
        "background_color": "#ffffff",
        "heading_color": "#1a1a1a",
        "text_color": "#555555",
        "show_button": true,
        "button_label": "Shop Solid Sheesham Wood Beds",
        "button_link": "shopify://collections/beds"
      }
    },
    "info_columns_J4Lbtk": {
      "type": "info-columns",
      "blocks": {
        "column_RUfGqg": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Rosewood_Finish_5f9f2696-cd42-43b1-825a-fd9eb9d15a30.png",
            "icon_size": 100,
            "icon_gap": 40,
            "heading": "Rosewood Finish",
            "text": "<p>Deep chocolate-brown tones that appear almost black in low light, with the wood grain subtly visible beneath the finish. The darkest option available, creating maximum drama and formality. Particularly striking in modern and minimalist spaces where the dark wood provides bold contrast. Hides minor wear and scratches better than lighter finishes while maintaining the authentic solid wood appearance.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "column_axLCHk": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Espresso_Brown_Finish_71f83e82-9edc-4fca-a1ce-86d6cc6b1393.png",
            "icon_size": 100,
            "icon_gap": 40,
            "heading": "Espresso Brown Finish",
            "text": "<p>The richest, most intense finish in the collection—deep espresso-to-black tones that create a dramatic, high-contrast look. The wood grain is still discernible but takes a secondary role to the bold color statement. Best suited for contemporary and modern bedrooms, especially those with lighter floors or walls where you want the bed to anchor the space visually. This finish makes the bed a focal point rather than blending with other furniture.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "column_VLPwzq": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Honey-Teak_Finish.png",
            "icon_size": 100,
            "icon_gap": 40,
            "heading": "Honey-Teak Finish (Sheesham Wood)",
            "text": "<p>Warm golden amber tones with pronounced grain patterns and natural color variation from light honey to deeper teak browns. The most versatile choice—works equally well with traditional carved designs and modern platform styles. Shows the authentic character of sheesham wood with visible knots and grain striping. Low-maintenance polyurethane coating that highlights the wood's natural beauty.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        },
        "column_UKCgcF": {
          "type": "column",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Dark-Teak_Finish.png",
            "icon_size": 100,
            "icon_gap": 40,
            "heading": "Dark-Teak Finish (Sheesham Wood)",
            "text": "<p>Rich medium-to-dark brown tones with subtle color gradation across the wood planks. Creates a sophisticated, grounded aesthetic without going fully dark. The natural grain remains visible, providing warmth and texture while offering a more refined appearance than lighter finishes. Excellent for contemporary bedrooms and pairs well with both neutral and bold wall colors.</p>",
            "card_background": "#f7f7f7"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "column_RUfGqg",
        "column_axLCHk",
